text: Gessica Turato (born 30 July 1984) is a track and road cyclist from Italy. As a junior, she won the individual pursuit at the 2001 UEC European Track Championships. She won the under-23 road race at the 2005 European Road Championships and represented her nation later that year at the 2005 UCI Road World Championships. ==References== ==External links== * profile at Procyclingstats.com Category:1984 births Category:Italian female cyclists Category:Living people Category:People from Cittadella
